WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Alhamdulillah, O Lord of the worlds

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.000
The Most Merciful, the Most Merciful

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Owner of the Day of Judgment

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.000
It is You we worship, and it is You we ask for help

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Guide us to the straight path

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:21.000
The path that You have bestowed upon them

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Not the one who is angry with them

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:35.140
Assalamu alaikum wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuhu

00:00:35.140 --> 00:00:37.140
In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful

00:00:37.140 --> 00:00:39.140
All praise is due to Allah, the Lord of the worlds

00:00:39.140 --> 00:00:42.140
And peace and blessings be upon the one sent to the worlds

00:00:42.140 --> 00:00:46.140
Our Prophet Muhammad, and upon his family, companions and followers

00:00:46.140 --> 00:00:49.140
And those who follow them with kindness until the Day of Judgment and after

00:00:49.140 --> 00:00:51.140
We praise Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:00:51.140 --> 00:00:55.140
We send complete blessings and salutations upon Muhammad peace be upon him

00:00:55.140 --> 00:00:58.140
And all his companions, his entire household

00:00:58.140 --> 00:01:01.140
May Allah bless them and may He bless every single one of us

00:01:01.140 --> 00:01:03.140
And grant us goodness, Ameen

00:01:03.140 --> 00:01:08.140
Beloved brothers and sisters, we pause for a moment in support of a brother of ours

00:01:08.140 --> 00:01:10.140
Who was martyred a few days ago

00:01:10.140 --> 00:01:13.140
Or should I say, precisely the day before yesterday

00:01:13.140 --> 00:01:16.140
Here in the northwestern province

00:01:16.140 --> 00:01:21.140
Whilst he was teased about the beard that he had grown

00:01:21.140 --> 00:01:25.140
And that resulted in an argument which resulted in a fight

00:01:25.140 --> 00:01:27.140
Which resulted in his murder

00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:30.140
We stand in solidarity with him, making dua for him

00:01:30.140 --> 00:01:31.140
We say

00:01:34.140 --> 00:01:36.140
May Allah grant him Jannah

00:01:36.140 --> 00:01:41.140
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant his family also the sabr and the patience

00:01:41.140 --> 00:01:46.140
That is required to bear this particular difficulty that has come in their direction

00:01:46.140 --> 00:01:49.140
But the good news is he was granted a month of Ramadan

00:01:49.140 --> 00:01:54.140
And at the same time, he died as a result of people teasing him

00:01:54.140 --> 00:01:59.140
Because of him uplifting the Sunnah of Muhammad peace be upon him

00:01:59.140 --> 00:02:01.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors

00:02:01.140 --> 00:02:06.140
A few days ago we were making mention of how we are so fortunate to be from amongst those

00:02:06.140 --> 00:02:09.140
Who can practice our deen so freely

00:02:09.140 --> 00:02:13.140
And here we have an incident that has come as a gash to us all

00:02:13.140 --> 00:02:16.140
And we feel it every single one of us without exception

00:02:16.140 --> 00:02:19.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us protection

00:02:19.140 --> 00:02:22.140
And may He really grant the deceased Jannah

00:02:22.140 --> 00:02:26.140
And the day He takes us away, may He grant us Jannah as well

00:02:27.140 --> 00:02:31.140
The Prophet ﷺ was also laughed at

00:02:31.140 --> 00:02:34.140
He was also scoffed at

00:02:34.140 --> 00:02:38.140
And all those who believed were also looked at in a way

00:02:38.140 --> 00:02:46.140
That was very very light on the part of the disbelievers and heavy in the hearts of the believers

00:02:46.140 --> 00:02:50.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect the women folk as well as the men folk

00:02:50.140 --> 00:02:51.140
The ummah at large

00:02:51.140 --> 00:02:53.140
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us peace

00:02:53.140 --> 00:02:57.140
Not only in this country or in this region but across the globe

00:02:57.140 --> 00:03:04.140
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless all those and protect those who are suffering in one way or another across the globe

00:03:04.140 --> 00:03:09.140
In the third year of Hijra there was something made prohibited

00:03:09.140 --> 00:03:13.140
Which was clarified very very clearly in the Quran

00:03:13.140 --> 00:03:15.140
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:36.140
Do not marry the polytheists no matter what

00:03:36.140 --> 00:03:41.140
It is prohibited to marry those who worship more than one deity

00:03:41.140 --> 00:03:46.140
Those who worship gods besides Allah or with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:03:47.140 --> 00:03:48.140
Totally prohibited

00:03:48.140 --> 00:03:55.140
Allah says to marry a slave girl who is believing is far better than to marry those who are polytheists

00:03:55.140 --> 00:03:57.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us

00:03:57.140 --> 00:04:00.140
And this is why Allah has prohibited it both ways

00:04:00.140 --> 00:04:04.140
Neither are the men allowed to marry women who are polytheists

00:04:04.140 --> 00:04:08.140
Nor are the women allowed to marry men who are polytheists

00:04:08.140 --> 00:04:09.140
That's the law

00:04:09.140 --> 00:04:12.140
It was dictated by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:04:12.140 --> 00:04:13.140
We do not ask questions

00:04:13.140 --> 00:04:16.140
Today people say sometimes why is it the case?

00:04:16.140 --> 00:04:21.140
Well common sense is if you cannot even come to common grounds on faith

00:04:21.140 --> 00:04:25.140
How are you going to come on common grounds with everything else?

00:04:25.140 --> 00:04:33.140
And this is why I usually like to give the example of people who have totally different diet requirements

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:38.140
For example you have a person who is on a seafood diet

00:04:38.140 --> 00:04:40.140
When we say seafood we mean the real seafood

00:04:40.140 --> 00:04:42.140
Not seafood as in he sees food and he eats

00:04:42.140 --> 00:04:43.140
No

00:04:43.140 --> 00:04:46.140
But rather seafood as in that which comes from the ocean

00:04:46.140 --> 00:04:50.140
And you have another person who is a vegetarian completely

00:04:50.140 --> 00:04:52.140
And the two of them get married

00:04:52.140 --> 00:04:56.140
The marriage may work but there will come a time when one will be fed up of the other

00:04:56.140 --> 00:05:02.140
Because for how long are you going to be having totally separate kitchens which have cooked totally separate items

00:05:02.140 --> 00:05:05.140
If we understand this about food

00:05:05.140 --> 00:05:07.140
What about deal which is far more important

00:05:08.140 --> 00:05:11.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect our generations

00:05:11.140 --> 00:05:14.140
And may he make us from amongst those who are not confused

00:05:14.140 --> 00:05:18.140
And at the same time may he grant us an understanding

00:05:18.140 --> 00:05:20.140
Thereafter in the fourth year of Hijra

00:05:20.140 --> 00:05:27.140
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam was blessed with another grandchild by the name of Al-Husayn ibn Ali radiallahu anhu

00:05:27.140 --> 00:05:30.140
Previous year he had been blessed with Al-Hasan ibn Ali

00:05:30.140 --> 00:05:34.140
So Al-Hasan wa Al-Husayn radiallahu anhum they were not twins

00:05:34.140 --> 00:05:38.140
But there was a gap of approximately a year between them

00:05:38.140 --> 00:05:41.140
The older being Al-Hasan ibn Ali radiallahu anhu

00:05:41.140 --> 00:05:44.140
The younger being Al-Husayn ibn Ali radiallahu anhu

00:05:44.140 --> 00:05:48.140
And this was a blessing the family of the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:05:48.140 --> 00:05:50.140
He was granted a grandson

00:05:50.140 --> 00:05:55.140
He had had another grandson known as Abdullah ibn Uthman radiallahu anhu

00:05:55.140 --> 00:05:57.140
Who had also passed away in infancy

00:05:57.140 --> 00:06:02.140
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to grant us children who will be the coolness of our eyes

00:06:02.140 --> 00:06:08.140
Who will also be able to serve the Deen in the same way that Al-Hasan wa Al-Husayn radiallahu anhum did

00:06:08.140 --> 00:06:12.140
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us Jannah

00:06:12.140 --> 00:06:16.140
For having looked after our children and given them the Deen

00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:18.140
Indeed it is something very great

00:06:18.140 --> 00:06:22.140
Sometimes we have to correct ourselves because I say

00:06:22.140 --> 00:06:25.140
We need and this is a fact

00:06:25.140 --> 00:06:29.140
Sometimes we need attention we need to be corrected

00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:35.140
And yet on our shoulders has been placed the duty of correcting our own children

00:06:35.140 --> 00:06:37.140
So we need to take it very seriously

00:06:37.140 --> 00:06:39.140
It's a big responsibility

00:06:39.140 --> 00:06:41.140
We should not be behaving like little children

00:06:41.140 --> 00:06:45.140
When Allah has blessed us already with children who look up to us for guidance

00:06:45.140 --> 00:06:48.140
Whilst we ourselves are still in search of guidance

00:06:48.140 --> 00:06:52.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala guide us and help us to guide our own children

00:06:52.140 --> 00:06:55.140
Then the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:06:55.140 --> 00:06:58.140
One of his brothers, foster brothers

00:06:58.140 --> 00:07:00.140
Whose name was Abu Salamah

00:07:00.140 --> 00:07:03.140
This Abu Salamah was the first person who made Hijrah

00:07:03.140 --> 00:07:06.140
If you recall his wife Umm Salamah

00:07:06.140 --> 00:07:09.140
Was the one who was separated from him when he was making Hijrah

00:07:09.140 --> 00:07:13.140
And his clan came and took the child away as well

00:07:13.140 --> 00:07:15.140
She was separated three ways

00:07:15.140 --> 00:07:17.140
One is she had lost

00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:18.140
Firstly she was on her own

00:07:18.140 --> 00:07:20.140
Secondly her husband was separated

00:07:20.140 --> 00:07:21.140
He was in Madina Munawwara

00:07:21.140 --> 00:07:24.140
The child was with the family of the husband

00:07:24.140 --> 00:07:26.140
And she was on her own being blocked

00:07:26.140 --> 00:07:28.140
She says she cried for more than a year

00:07:28.140 --> 00:07:30.140
If you recall we mentioned it a few days ago

00:07:30.140 --> 00:07:32.140
And this Umm Salamah

00:07:32.140 --> 00:07:33.140
Radhiallahu anha

00:07:33.140 --> 00:07:36.140
Her name was Hind binti Abi Umayyah

00:07:36.140 --> 00:07:38.140
She lost her husband Abu Salamah

00:07:38.140 --> 00:07:44.140
And a beautiful discussion had taken place between them before his death

00:07:44.140 --> 00:07:46.140
You see sometimes husband and wife get together

00:07:46.140 --> 00:07:48.140
And they discuss and they chat out of love

00:07:48.140 --> 00:07:51.140
And they say you know if I die don't marry anyone else

00:07:51.140 --> 00:07:53.140
And the other one says if you die

00:07:53.140 --> 00:07:55.140
I won't marry anyone else

00:07:55.140 --> 00:07:59.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us spouses who are the coolness of our eyes

00:07:59.140 --> 00:08:00.140
So Umm Salamah says

00:08:00.140 --> 00:08:01.140
Oh Abu Salamah

00:08:01.140 --> 00:08:04.140
If you were to die I wouldn't marry again

00:08:04.140 --> 00:08:07.140
I've heard that you would be in paradise with your spouse

00:08:07.140 --> 00:08:09.140
And so I won't marry again

00:08:09.140 --> 00:08:12.140
Who will be as good as you?

00:08:12.140 --> 00:08:13.140
Oh Abu Salamah

00:08:13.140 --> 00:08:15.140
Who is there that can be as good as you

00:08:15.140 --> 00:08:19.140
In your trustworthiness, your honor, your dignity, your iman

00:08:19.140 --> 00:08:21.140
Your sacrifice and so on

00:08:21.140 --> 00:08:22.140
And Abu Salamah said

00:08:22.140 --> 00:08:23.140
Oh Allah

00:08:23.140 --> 00:08:26.140
When I die grant her a better husband than me

00:08:26.140 --> 00:08:27.140
Subhanallah

00:08:27.140 --> 00:08:28.140
This was a dua

00:08:28.140 --> 00:08:31.140
And although Umm Salamah was quite reluctant

00:08:31.140 --> 00:08:34.140
It is reported that after he passed away and after the iddah

00:08:34.140 --> 00:08:37.140
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radhiallahu anhu had proposed to her

00:08:37.140 --> 00:08:39.140
Or had requested

00:08:39.140 --> 00:08:41.140
And she politely turned it down

00:08:41.140 --> 00:08:42.140
Showed a disinterest

00:08:42.140 --> 00:08:45.140
The same applies to Umar bint Al-Khattab radhiallahu anhu

00:08:45.140 --> 00:08:47.140
According to the books of history

00:08:47.140 --> 00:08:49.140
They say that she had politely said no

00:08:49.140 --> 00:08:52.140
Until a day came when the Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:08:52.140 --> 00:08:55.140
Proposed for Umm Salamah radhiallahu anhu

00:08:55.140 --> 00:08:57.140
One of the reasons was

00:08:57.140 --> 00:08:59.140
She was obviously a widow

00:08:59.140 --> 00:09:01.140
She was older than Muhammad salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:09:01.140 --> 00:09:04.140
And she had made this quite clear

00:09:04.140 --> 00:09:06.140
When she accepted the proposal

00:09:06.140 --> 00:09:07.140
Look I'm older than you

00:09:07.140 --> 00:09:10.140
But at the same time it was her sacrifice for the deen

00:09:10.140 --> 00:09:13.140
She was one of those who sacrificed so much

00:09:13.140 --> 00:09:17.140
And she had had a great respect

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:20.140
Amongst the believers male and female

00:09:20.140 --> 00:09:23.140
And the Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam did not want to leave her

00:09:23.140 --> 00:09:25.140
As a woman who had no guardian and so on

00:09:25.140 --> 00:09:28.140
So the Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam proposed for her

00:09:28.140 --> 00:09:29.140
And he married her

00:09:29.140 --> 00:09:32.140
Salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:09:32.140 --> 00:09:36.140
Thereafter hostilities began once again

00:09:36.140 --> 00:09:39.140
In the fourth year of Hijra in Safar

00:09:39.140 --> 00:09:41.140
Prior to this there were a few skirmishes

00:09:41.140 --> 00:09:43.140
Where you find some people had come in

00:09:43.140 --> 00:09:44.140
They tried to harm

00:09:44.140 --> 00:09:47.140
And the Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam sent a small army

00:09:47.140 --> 00:09:49.140
Or a platoon to deal with them and so on

00:09:49.140 --> 00:09:52.140
In this particular instance there was

00:09:52.140 --> 00:09:55.140
Some people who had come to Al-Madeen Al-Munawarah

00:09:55.140 --> 00:09:57.140
And they had requested that

00:09:57.140 --> 00:09:59.140
The Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam sent with them

00:09:59.140 --> 00:10:02.140
Some companions to teach them the Quran

00:10:02.140 --> 00:10:05.140
And so the Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam sent

00:10:05.140 --> 00:10:08.740
Ten of his companions

00:10:08.740 --> 00:10:09.740
From amongst them was

00:10:10.740 --> 00:10:14.740
He sent them to a place known as Al-Rajiyah

00:10:14.740 --> 00:10:17.740
And what had happened

00:10:17.740 --> 00:10:21.740
The people who had come requesting in Madinah Al-Munawarah

00:10:21.740 --> 00:10:25.740
They were a group of people from Adal and Al-Qara

00:10:25.740 --> 00:10:27.740
Adal and Al-Qara, two little clans

00:10:27.740 --> 00:10:31.740
The Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam sent with them ten people

00:10:31.740 --> 00:10:35.740
When they went on the road, on the path

00:10:35.740 --> 00:10:37.740
These people changed their mind

00:10:37.740 --> 00:10:39.740
They executed all ten companions

00:10:39.740 --> 00:10:40.740
And this was a disaster

00:10:40.740 --> 00:10:43.740
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:44.740
This was a disaster

00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:46.740
They sought the assistance of Hudayl

00:10:46.740 --> 00:10:48.740
Hudayl was a tribe

00:10:48.740 --> 00:10:50.740
And they sought their assistance

00:10:50.740 --> 00:10:51.740
They executed them

00:10:51.740 --> 00:10:54.740
Similar time, round about similar time

00:10:54.740 --> 00:10:56.740
There was a group of people

00:10:56.740 --> 00:10:59.740
With a leader known as Amir ibn Malik

00:10:59.740 --> 00:11:01.740
He had come from Najd

00:11:01.740 --> 00:11:03.740
And he did not accept Islam

00:11:03.740 --> 00:11:06.740
But he had come to Muhammad salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:11:06.740 --> 00:11:09.740
He heard about Islam and he was very keen

00:11:09.740 --> 00:11:12.740
And he said, look, why don't you send a group of people to Najd

00:11:12.740 --> 00:11:15.740
The Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam says, I fear the people of Najd

00:11:15.740 --> 00:11:16.740
They might harm my people

00:11:16.740 --> 00:11:18.740
He says, I give my guarantee

00:11:18.740 --> 00:11:20.740
With my guarantee, nothing will happen

00:11:20.740 --> 00:11:23.740
And as you know at that time, the guarantees used to work

00:11:23.740 --> 00:11:27.740
So the Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam sent with them

00:11:27.740 --> 00:11:29.740
Seventy qurra

00:11:29.740 --> 00:11:31.740
Qurra meaning those reciters of the Quran

00:11:31.740 --> 00:11:33.740
Who knew the Quran very very well

00:11:33.740 --> 00:11:37.740
And as they left, they got to a place known as

00:11:37.740 --> 00:11:38.740
Bi'ri Ma'unah

00:11:38.740 --> 00:11:40.740
Where the well of Ma'unah was

00:11:40.740 --> 00:11:43.740
And what had happened at that particular place

00:11:43.740 --> 00:11:47.740
The group of Muslims sent

00:11:47.740 --> 00:11:48.740
Haram ibn Malhan

00:11:48.740 --> 00:11:49.740
He was one of them

00:11:49.740 --> 00:11:51.740
Radhiallahu anha Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:11:51.740 --> 00:11:52.740
Grant him goodness

00:11:52.740 --> 00:11:55.740
He was sent with a letter

00:11:55.740 --> 00:11:57.740
To the leader of Bani Amir

00:11:57.740 --> 00:11:59.740
Whose name was Amir ibn al-Tufail

00:11:59.740 --> 00:12:01.740
And this Amir ibn al-Tufail

00:12:01.740 --> 00:12:02.740
Amir ibn al-Tufail

00:12:02.740 --> 00:12:03.740
He had had this letter

00:12:03.740 --> 00:12:04.740
Without reading it

00:12:04.740 --> 00:12:06.740
He heard these people are Muslimin

00:12:06.740 --> 00:12:08.740
He executed this man

00:12:08.740 --> 00:12:09.740
For no reason

00:12:09.740 --> 00:12:10.740
Now this doesn't happen

00:12:10.740 --> 00:12:13.740
You do not execute an ambassador

00:12:13.740 --> 00:12:15.740
An ambassador is there to present a message

00:12:15.740 --> 00:12:17.740
You either accept it or reject it

00:12:17.740 --> 00:12:19.740
Or you give back whatever you have to say

00:12:19.740 --> 00:12:21.740
Either positive or negative

00:12:21.740 --> 00:12:23.740
And you let him proceed

00:12:23.740 --> 00:12:25.740
From that time up to this day

00:12:25.740 --> 00:12:29.740
It is very very unacceptable

00:12:29.740 --> 00:12:32.740
To kill an ambassador or execute a messenger

00:12:32.740 --> 00:12:33.740
Who has come to you with a message

00:12:33.740 --> 00:12:35.740
Imagine a postman comes to you

00:12:35.740 --> 00:12:36.740
With a message of someone else

00:12:36.740 --> 00:12:37.740
And you execute him

00:12:37.740 --> 00:12:38.740
Because you don't like the message

00:12:38.740 --> 00:12:41.740
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us

00:12:41.740 --> 00:12:42.740
If that was the case

00:12:42.740 --> 00:12:43.740
We wouldn't have postmen at all

00:12:43.740 --> 00:12:45.740
Allahu Akbar

00:12:45.740 --> 00:12:47.740
So when that happened

00:12:47.740 --> 00:12:49.740
It caused a little bit of a disaster

00:12:49.740 --> 00:12:52.740
These were 70 men from amongst the Muslimin

00:12:52.740 --> 00:12:56.740
And this man who had killed

00:12:56.740 --> 00:12:57.740
Haram ibn Malhan

00:12:57.740 --> 00:12:58.740
What he did is

00:12:58.740 --> 00:12:59.740
He called his people

00:12:59.740 --> 00:13:00.740
Banu Amir

00:13:00.740 --> 00:13:02.740
That come, let's come to my assistance

00:13:02.740 --> 00:13:05.740
Because the rest of them are going to come and attack

00:13:05.740 --> 00:13:06.740
Banu Amir said no

00:13:06.740 --> 00:13:10.740
These people have the guarantee of Amir ibn Malik

00:13:10.740 --> 00:13:13.740
So we are not going to assist against him

00:13:13.740 --> 00:13:16.740
And against them

00:13:16.740 --> 00:13:17.740
And when that happened

00:13:17.740 --> 00:13:19.740
This man Amir ibn Tufail

00:13:19.740 --> 00:13:23.740
He called some other tribes and clans from nearby

00:13:23.740 --> 00:13:24.740
Come and help

00:13:24.740 --> 00:13:25.740
Who were they?

00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:26.740
The tribe of R'al

